tweet: A small note: this happened about a year after my dad's death. When a person of Buddhist religion dies, the monks come and bless their house. They wrap a string around the entirety of the house to protect it from spirits entering the house.

name: David
tweet: The silhouette of the man still showed up with his knife. I still didn't panic. In my head, I just accepted death. If he was going to kill me then there was literally nothing I could do about it. I remember thinking "fuck it, if you're gonna kill me then do it."

name: David
tweet: Not fear from the man just watching me with a knife, but because I was helpless. I couldn't move, couldn't yell, couldn't do anything about it. That was the most fearful part.

name: David
tweet: That's when I saw something next to me. It was a tall, dark silhouette. It resembled a man with a circular hat on. He was holding a knife, just standing over me watching. Let me tell you that I've never experienced such fear.
